Authors: Dzulfiqar Agung M.R., Elian A.A., Astuti W., Puji M.N.
Title: Development of Fish Separator Conveyor based on Fish Identification System
Source title: IOP Conference Series: Earth and Environmental Science
Affiliations: Automotive and Robotics Program, Computer Engineering Department, BINUS ASO School of Engineering, Bina Nusantara University, Jakarta, 11480, Indonesia
Authors with affiliations: Dzulfiqar Agung, M.R., Automotive and Robotics Program, Computer Engineering Department, BINUS ASO School of Engineering, Bina Nusantara University, Jakarta, 11480, Indonesia; Elian, A.A., Automotive and Robotics Program, Computer Engineering Department, BINUS ASO School of Engineering, Bina Nusantara University, Jakarta, 11480, Indonesia; Astuti, W., Automotive and Robotics Program, Computer Engineering Department, BINUS ASO School of Engineering, Bina Nusantara University, Jakarta, 11480, Indonesia; Puji, M.N., Automotive and Robotics Program, Computer Engineering Department, BINUS ASO School of Engineering, Bina Nusantara University, Jakarta, 11480, Indonesia
Abstract: Indonesia as the largest archipelago and maritime country in the world has a very large marine resources. Fish is one of the marine wealthties (marine biota), which have large numbers in Indonesia. Fishermen is an important role in the process of fishing, however fish caught by fishermen are often mixed with other types of fish. Currently, the process of fist separation is done manually, which takes longer time and many error occur due to fatigue. In this work the conveyer separator based on the fish identification system is developed. The fish conveyer separator is designed and developed. The fish identification system is based on Fast Fourier Transform (FTT) technique and Artificial Neural Network (ANN). The system is working properly, since it resulting the training and testing accuracy of 80% and 66%, respectively. © 2020 Published under licence by IOP Publishing Ltd.
Author Keywords: Artificial Neural Network; Automated Conveyor; Fast Fourier Transform

Title: Development of automatic painful detection based on the face recognition system
Source title: Proceedings of the International Conference on Industrial Engineering and Operations Management
Affiliations: Computer Engineering Department, BINUS ASO School of Engineering, Bina Nusantara University, Jakarta, 11480, Indonesia; Nursery Departement, Cilacap Regional General Hospital, Gatot Subroto No.28, Cilacap, Central Jawa  53223, Indonesia

Abstract: Pain is an unpleasant emotional experience caused by tissue damage. Pain is subjective, where each individual has a different pain response, sometimes difficult to express and can only be felt by the individual without being felt by others. Therefore, the assessment of pain for each treatment by medical personnel can be different. This could lead to non-standard handling of patients in pain medical treatment. The automatic stand alone system for pain detection based on face recognition is developed. The system determines patient paint level detector based on facial expression recognition. The face detection is based on face image procession technique and Convolution Neural Network (CNN). The system is working properly, since it resulting the training and testing accuracy of 90% and 70%, respectively. © IEOM Society International.
Author Keywords: Artificial Neural Network; Automated stand alone embedded system; Facial expression technique
